ABUJA – The Supreme Court on Friday dismissed an appeal filed by a former Governor of Rivers state Rt Hon. Rotimi Amaechi. By the suit, Amaechi, the immediate past Minister of Transportation, wants the apex court to restrain the Rivers state government from probing him in the alleged N96bn fraud and fraudulent sales of valued assets belonging to the State government. Amaechi, a presidential aspirant under the flagship of the All Progressives Congress had lost at the High Court of Rivers State and Court of Appeal, which prompted his case at the Supreme Court. -Advertisement- However, Governor Nyesom Wike of Rivers state who had constituted a 7-man panel to probe Amaechi, is, asking the Supreme Court to dismiss Amaechi’s suit. A seven-man panel led by Justice Olukayode Ariwoola, slated the date for judgment after various counsel in the matter had made final submission on Monday. Specifically, By the appeal, Amaechi had prayed the Supreme Court to restrain Governor Nyesom Wike from investigating his eight-year tenure as governor of the state. Bur delivering judgment on the appeal on Friday, the Apex court unanimously dismissed Amaechi’s appeal for lacking in merit.